1 WHEREAS, Drug addiction can fuel feelings of shame, guilt, embarrassment,
2 depression, and hopelessness, causing individuals to resist seeking treatment and support;
3 and
4 WHEREAS, Overdose Awareness Day is a global event held August 31 each year
5 that aims to raise awareness of drug overdoses, reduce the stigma of a drug–related death,
6 and acknowledge the grief felt by families and friends remembering those who have died or
7 had a permanent injury as a result of a drug overdose; and
8 WHEREAS, Recognizing Overdose Awareness Day in Maryland sends a strong
9 message to former or current substance users, namely, that they are valued, and that
10 overdose death is preventable; now, therefore,
11 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
12 That Section(s) 7–416 through 7–421 of Article – General Provisions of the Annotated Code
13 of Maryland be renumbered to be Section(s) 7–417 through 7–422, respectively.
14 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That the Laws of Maryland read
15 as follows:
16 Article – General Provisions
17 7–416.
18 THE GOVERNOR ANNUALLY SHALL PROCLAIM AUGUST 31 AS OVERDOSE
19 AWARENESS DAY.
20 SECTION 3. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect July
21 1, 2025.

